2. Property resolver <property (old way )  to @Value ( new way )
3. npm list ( dependency tree )
4. Java... 
  using -D at command line adds it to JVM system properties that can be see via System.getProperties(). 
  From code to add system property do System.setProperty().
  From Tomcat catalina.properties also lets you set system properties.
  From spring to access system properties do
    @Autowired
    private Environment env;
    ...
    dataSource.setUrl(env.getProperty("jdbc.url"));
